reviews.text: Took the 3-cheese tortelloni rosa pasta. It's really good. The ambience is great and the service is amazing. Great for a decent dinner. Recommendation : Would like larger portion sizes.
Got the Thai Noodles (small) here. It was ok. The noodles were a bit hard to bite into. The place is huge and has a paid parking outside.

Don't really care about the negative reviews regarding customer service. The pasta isn't always cooked properly and they skimp very much on the sauce which makes the undercooked pasta that much worse. Even when I asked for extra sauce (and paid for it), they forgot and I had to go back and tell them. Even then it wasn't enough to mask the issue of just poorly prepped food. I've had maybe 1 or 2 decent experiences with the food here out of about 10 or so visits.

If you want to having dining hall food for $10, this is your place. The bad reviews are here for a reason. For the same price you could be eating significantly better food at Cava. The food is very poor quality and tasteless. My friend even had hair in his food and they wouldn’t refund it.
Soda machine is always out of order. Food is automatically placed in to-go containers. Some entrées have small portions. Way too expensive.
Got a classic burger, wanted medium rare, came back well done and cold. Also no seasoning at all. Did get a lot of tots. Good for college kids to drink at, not great food.

This place is a great college sports bar with lots of tvs to catch your team.  Decent but limited beer selection.  Top notch fried food - good wings and great tots menu items.  The staff is friendly, bartenders are helpful. Have fun!

This place used to be great for lunch and happy hours.  Ever since “covid” they say, this place has completely changed for the worse and is terrible.  They jacked up their prices to an insane amount and the food is average at best.  They don’t have any happy hour specials anymore due to “covid” as the bar tender told me.  This place used to be packed during happy hours and during the weekdays and today was completely empty.

So I guess the owner is a genius… raise prices to make more money but deter everyone from coming because prices are too high and ohh wait… now I’m not making any money.

It’s prob a good spot for college kids to drink but if you’re looking for a place to eat and grab a beer, I’d go elsewhere.
What else to expect from a college bar. Better for those looking for only drinks than food. Took over an hour to get our meal, which was average at best.

The food wasn’t what I expected. Fries tasted like funnel cake, and the chili was lukewarm. Our server suggested that she could take the chili back to “reheat” it but the chili came back the same. I also had the Cornerstone Wings, and they were surprisingly edible. If you expect good quality food at any restaurant, I wouldn’t recommend this place due to them not caring for my satisfaction. If you’re trying to get drinks only, sure why not... Server didn’t meet my expectations. You don’t see your check until you pay (electronically).

I like coming the most  to this chipotle  to the fact  that they give you way more  food than other corporations in other areas i recommend  .  Go in the 2 or 3 pm that crew is great workers friendly  environment  .  I order a burrito  and came out to be a great size that they had to wrapped  twice with the flour tortilla  and i didnt add any extra .  Burrito was wrapped  correctly  .

I just bought 5 bowls of double meat chicken and steak borito bowls to go and I wish I can return them now. The chicken and steak are all old and stale and not as good as I know it to be. As I sat down at home blaming myself for not going to a different Chipotle location instead, I realized that colleges students from UMCP who are their major customer base are closed from school and therefore patronage is comparably low for them. But damn, why will you still sell a food that have been sitting there so long and has gotten old and stale? That is unfair and I demand a complete refund of the over $70 that I spent. I am absolutely not satisfied 😒. Worse of all, the lady serving the food was talking too much over the food and she had no mask on. Omg what a day! If she loves to talk that much, then she must put on the mask when serving the food please!

Hit or miss location. Place is really dirty, stations a mess, food under cooked or they stiff you on portion size. Wait is always pretty quick even with a super long line. Chorizo and other speciality meats may not be in stock at times. Best to get to the front and ask ahead to see if they'll have what you want

The only reason why this place gets any customers is because it's the only one near UMD. everytime I get a burrito here it always ends up being smaller, sloppier, and more poorly wrapped than the last. I hate that this is the only chipotle I have Access to, I really makes me think about the time I've spent in highschool and how things could have been if I went to a BETTER university, with, most importantly, a BETTER CHIPOTLE. This cs program doesn't even seem worth it if all my burritos are gonna be 1 star disappointments for the next 4 years. This chipotle makes me want to graduate early. This chipotle makes me want to work harder so I can transfer to a better school with a better chipotle. This chipotle is a personal representation of failure. Definitely deserves 0 stars, but 1 star will have to do for now.
Chipotle is Chipotle. What differs from time to time is the amount of food served. This particular evening the portion of steak in a steak bowl was pretty *small*.

I Came Here For A Quick Lunch. I Ordered A Pizza Through The App For CarryOut, But Then Decided To Dine In & I Ordered A Caesar Salad(I Added Tomato & Onion). I Have Been To This Specific Location Multiple Times. The Appetizers Are Great. Pizza Is Great. They Have A Full Bar At This Location. The Service Was Not That Great(I Was Not Pleased With The Server). But The Food Was Good.
That thin crush tastes like pastry. As such, this local staple is a favorite among people from Maryland. The pizza lives up to expectations, and that pepperoni pizza is deadly good.

This was an original Ledo's, but they revamped the restaurant and changed the menu. Not really impressed. The restaurant itself is in excellent condition, and very clean. Bathrooms included. The service is top notch. Our waitress was amazing. But the food was just not it. My husband loves it, so I gave an extra star but personally it's a 3 for me, tastewise. There is parking at this location and a bar. I preferred the restaurant at its former glory so please take this with a grain of salt.
There is parking in the back of the building but it's a little creepy at night.

I wanted to try the pizza here, now that they are under new ownership (Ledo Pizza). I ordered a specialty pizza for carryout, with fresh basil & chicken & 4 cheeses. Seems to be the "Spring Chicken Pizza" on the current menu, but I honestly don't remember that name. It was delicious, it really was, and I really wanted to like it... but the crust just wasn't the same. I don't know if maybe they use a different type of crust for different pizzas, but I've not found any information +/-. That and my extras weren't included, which I didn't realize until sitting in traffic on the way home. I know, I should have checked at pickup, but I was running late and too hurried, the usual.
Spring Chicken Pizza
Garlic herb aioli sauce, basil leaves, sliced chicken topped with smoked Provolone, Fontina, Asiago and Parmesan cheese. Garnished with fresh basil.
Full disclosure: Ledo's Restaurant was my favorite MD Pizza, and I was very sad to learn that they had closed. I'd been happily inhaling their pizza for a good number of years, first enjoyed them at their original location in Adelphi a few {ahem} quality years ago and was thrilled when they moved to College Park. Fear the Turtle! 🐢 I can say I understand, they provided some *** good Pizza for a good number of years, so I have nothing but the best thoughts of and for the original owners. Thanks for the great memories. ♥️🤍🖤💛

Cozy atmosphere with delicious pizza at an affordable price. Cindy our server could not have been nicer. She was attentive, super friendly, and makes you look forward to coming back. All around great restaurant for some Maryland pizza.

name: Starbucks
vicinity: Shopping Center, 7336 Baltimore Avenue, College Park

reviews.text: Lovely baristas, extremely polite and good service. Their timings are perfect for a college town. I enjoy the music and go there often to work.

Crazy homeless people hang out at this place all the time. They take up half the seats and sit in the same seats for hours every without purchasing anything. It's been getting worse every year. Usually I wouldn't mind, but some of them are unpredictable and start yelling at random people, soliciting money and sometimes it's really terrifying.
Don't come here if you expect to find a seat because it's always filled with college students too. Some stay for hours without buying anything.
The employees are very nice though despite being very overworked.

Came in today for an online order. There were so many people I wanted to die can't even imagine how the workers must feel. They're incredible got my drink, made correctly, and so speedy. Major major shout out to everyone working there, you guys are truly warriors.
This is easily the best Starbucks I've ever been to. The drink quality is high, but the service is even better. The staff works actively to curate a fun and welcoming environment.

Very utilitarian Starbucks.  I have been in literally hundreds of Starbucks over 20 years and this one is really lacking in atmosphere, but they make a decent coffee and the service is good. It's really a simple in and out place although there are always a couple of easy chairs if you want to sit there for a while and people watch. Lots of college kids studying on their laptops.

First time today around lunch time. Me and my beast friend wanted to try something new. Ally our waiter was absolutely AMAZING! If I get to return I’m asking for her. We had the buffalo chicken dip (DELICIOUS), looney fries, onion rings , old bay wings, and chicken tenders. Everything was great! Chicken tenders were basic but everything else I would order again. That was about $70 bucks. But worth it! Ally checked in on us but without being annoying and I appreciate that anywhere I go! You have to pay to park so be prepared. I hope I can come back but it was a damn near perfect dine in experience. Give ally a raise for being awesome please thank you management .
Nice experience. Not to crowded but getting a little pricey. If you are a sports fan it's your place. If you are a Terps fan... nothing better. Great staff and food is excellent. Consistent.

There is nothing bad that I can say at all. The bartender was friendly and the drinks were right. The food was really good and the portions were huge. The DJ had a good mix going. It was just an awesome vibe

Love this place for the drink specials, motts sticks and quesadillas. Around a college so can be a pretty young crowd. There was a short wait for us but extended to like thirty to 45 mins so prep for a possible wait. Pay for the parking because they will tow ya ishhh!
Went on a Thursday this time and honestly I felt super old because 3/4 of people in there had on backpacks and whewwwwee flashback to college central. But great to watch games- nice sized bar!
Oh and when I checked on Yelp gave me 10 percent off to use- but uhm Yelp y’all need to touch base with looneys bc they said this is like something old or they haven’t heard from you so mhmhm. But the manager was super nice about it and honored it so great customer service.

the service was pretty quick! we went there for happy hour and we got the orange crush buckets, the crab dip and the nachos - all of them had very huge portions! the three of us barely finished the two apps !
Cool spot really disappointed in the general manager shoddiness and poor work ethic.  Hopefully he can gro some empathy.  Excellent service from cam and josh.
Lots of college  memories here but food average   college joint but the vibe is fantastic. Can’t believe it’s still here after 35 years.

Cute place! I liked the atmosphere in the outdoor area. The food was pretty good as well. However, there was an issue as the kitchen got my order wrong, they gave me a sandwich instead of a bowl and grilled chicken instead of fried chicken.

Drinks were slow, beer from draught was lukewarm.  Not bad for a college bar.  Ordered brunch, found out 15 minutes later that they don’t serve brunch.  Found out from a friend, no toilet paper in the ladies restrooms.

The bouncers are actually the worst. Add in the crowds and its not even worth the bother. Save your ten dollars. There's gotta be somewhere better that doesn't check ideas. 3ff this place straight up.

name: Pho Thom
vicinity: 7313 Baltimore Avenue Ste F, College Park

reviews.text: Went here to try Vietnamese Pho for the first time. Had a great experience. Tried the steamed vegetarian dumplings as an appetizer. For the main course, I ordered the shrimp pho. Food was very flavorful & filling for under $20 per person! Would definitely recommend & will be returning.

I love this place, but surprisingly not for the pho! They have the BEST curry & the thom Ka chicken soup is literally to die for. So good 10/10. Their tom yum soup is pretty good too! Pho isn’t my top fav but pretty good as well. I’ve ordered here so much and never plan to stop! Yummy yummy YUMMY

THE ICED TEA WAS PHENOMENAL. GREAT PHO, WAS AFFORDABLE AND HAD A NICE ATMOSPHERE. THE BROTH IS THE BEST PART, HANDS DOWN. WILL BE RETURNING. I ALSO REALLY LIKE PLUM SAUCE 👍 I TAKE THAT HOME IN THE TO-GO CONTAINER AND PUT A LOT OF PLUM SAUCE IN DAT. THANKS FOR A GREAT EXPERIENCE!
Nice choice of pho and other south Asian dishes. The pho broth was particularly good.  I had the red curry with pork which was good. Next time I will definitely choose the pho.
Average soup(meaning good) to other restaurants I have ate before. I do Recommend  the Vietnamese coffee.

Likely the best sushi in the area. A key tell tale is great sushi rice!! I could eat a huge bowl of just the sushi rice! The fish are shipped in fresh and the rolls are innovative with fun names. They've also got great udon. Not to mention it's a local Mom and Pop shop with super nice owners ❤️

Hello Japanese food lovers - hurry over to Hanami while the holiday specials are still featured in the menu! I ordered Christmas Tree Roll and Holly Jolly Roll. Wow! These are really substantial layered treats! The two together made a scrumptious and rib-sticking lunch. And I have to say their decor is so pretty and charming. Their holiday window is gorgeous! This is the nicest sushi place for miles around, and very convenient to University of Maryland and downtown College Park. Enjoy your end-of-holidays meal!

They are my new fav sushi place in the area now! The sushi is fresh and delicious and the lady was nice to explain me the menu for some combos. I end up got the 3 rolls with miso soup. All the rolls look delicious and also taste great! Even the miso soup is very flavorful unlike some places will watered it down. Thank you for making my Sunday late lunch enjoyable!
Out of this world sushi. 11/10 recommend the sunny roll. Amazing and kind staff. The restaurant has such a cool atmosphere and it smells SO good when you walk in.

amazing sushi place tucked away in this college town. great menu with creative rolls and the classics. i recommend the iso roll. the quality is still first class even though it's been around for over 17 years. very reasonably priced and also a great place for small groups.

Visiting the area and ordered through Ubereats. I got the chicken gyro combo and a desert. The gyro was absolutely out of this world, from the flavor and tenderness of the chicken, the fluffy pita, to the amazing sauces. 10/10 definitely recommend. The fries were cold by the time I got them which is no fault of their own, but still had great flavor and the marathon sauce is to die for. If I ordered delivery again I would just stick with the gyro if in a hotel with no microwave. If ordering there at the restaurant definitely get the fries. For desert I ordered baklava but I guess they were out so I got kadaifi. It was super sweet so not totally my thing, but still ate it!

My first time hitting marathon Deli to grab lunch in the middle of my work day.  I much prefer the chilled out atmosphere and absence of crowds (like with late nights).

As I recall, I had a chicken gyro sandwich.  It was very good and I sat inside at the bar and had my meal alongside other construction workers.

Great working man's lunch spot.

Marathon is in a convenient location, stays open very late, and is very consistent in quality. Their gyros are great, their fries are very good, and everything else is at least good. It is LOUD in there. It's meant for college kids, for sure.

If the gyros and the fries were about a dollar or two cheaper, this would be five stars. The individual pizza is a really good deal.

Sad to see that it had moved from it's former location. The new owner was very nice. The gyro was good. The fries could have used a little more seasoning. It was just strange to see it offering a lot of non-Greek offerings.
So happy the tradition continues. Delicious lamb and chicken gyros. Really solid salad options for those inclined. Deliciously seasoned fries. Don’t forget the baklava!

Its the worst ebi soup noodle I have tasted, first bite of shrimp and noodle soup i had to spit it out, discusting. If i could rate this lower it would be below freezing of -10. I also ordered sushi for my wife, she dont want to try it at all...it all went to trash.

Small, simple asian restaurant that offers a wide range of asian fare. Sushi, Tempura, Bubble Tea etc. Customer service was fine. Table service is minimal.  All dishes are made to order.  If you like coffee the Cappuccino Bubble Tea is fantastic. I highly recommend this place for a casual bite to eat, or carryout.

Pretty good sushi, very fresh. Miso soup was great. I had the crazy roll and shrimp tempura. Wish the crazy roll was crunchier. Stays open until midnight and in the cut so you can avoid the craziness of all the bar people/college kids. Will go again!

I ordered Salmon sushi and sashimi through Uber Eats. Benishouga (pink pickled ginger) was gone bad and I could smell and see white fungus on the surface. I didn't eat Benishouga but the actual food might have touched the fungus when everything inside the food container was squished together (probably because of car riding?).

Great sushi and fast delivery, but...  I didn't like the sushi pizza, I don't understand the love for it, the one I got was an awful, lettuce-laden mess and I threw it out after two slices.  Ramen is just ok.
All the other Jimmy John's I've been to have been amazing service and fast. But this one was very slow and the service wasn't great.

So 1st let me say I LOOOOVE JJ food. It's why I continue to go back. But this College Park location has gone waaay down in customer service.
I walked into the store. There was a guy slicing meat at the meat counter amd a lady preparing the dough for the bread.
Then some other guy dressed in sweats and a t-shirt with his headphones in his ears, comes our of no where and asks me what I want.
I told him a #9 with no hot peppers.
He says #9 doesn't come with hot peppers anyway. The #7 does

I said oh ok. Well, either way, I want a #9, no hot peppers.

He says is that it?

No, I'll have another #9 on lettuce. No tomatoes. And these 2 bags of chips.

He looks at me and says "what no drinks!!?" With an attitude!

I said NO. NO drinks.....now I say it with an attitude.

He rings me up and repeats the order. They start preparing the order and I asked for extra dressing.

They had NO nice-ness. NO cordial-ness. NO smiles...at ALL.
They didn't used to be this way at this store.

Unfortunately, it's the only store close by now, since the other one down the street closed. But I don't like the "I don't give 2 sh*ts" attitude.

I ordered my food at 12:30PM and I watched the status change online to being delivered at 12:48PM. I waited until 1:27 and still no delivery. (I live less than mile from JJ.) I called and the person who picked up said that the driver left 5 mins ago, which was sus to me. Then I waited until 1:47 and still no food. So I asked for a refund. Posting this here to document in case I don't actually receive my refund, like I didn't receive my order.
Great delivery service, very speedy sandwich and pickle delivery, food was delicious. 0% sog, 100% sandwich 10/10 cute delivery guy

I placed an online order on 5/18/2022 and order was confirmed via email. Once I arrived to pick-up my order (College Park, MD location), the doors were locked. I called the store and there is no answer and the message says the phone has been disconnected. I called back on 5/19/2022 and no response, same issue. Make it right Jimmy Johns, I just want my subs, Jersey Mike’s would never
They make yummy sandwiches for your tummy!  Get there before the rush though or you might be waiting a while.  Love thier shakes too!
Horrendous!!! The sandwich was horrible. I ordered a BLTA and it has 2 small pieces of bacon no avocado and the tomatoes were soggy, Lettuce was dead AND It was eaten. Worse sandwich ever.

Very friendly staff. I had the skinny pair, Turkey and swiss sandwich with a cup of the tomato soup. The sandwich was delicious. I enjoyed the soup but was not the greatest. Parking is a challenge, you have to pay for it and there is not a lot of parking around.

Summary: Picked-up for Catering Order - Charged 25% more than the quote we were provided with no explanation. Sandwiches were good.

We hosted a party and so ordered a lot of sandwiches and salads.  We picked up the order (no delivery).  We were quoted a price and accepted.  We were told it included tax and tip.
We had a friend pick up the food.  When we saw the charge on our credit card, it was just over 25% more than what we were provided for our quote.  We have inquired regarding the price discrepancy, but it has been over a week and no answers have been provided.

The sandwiches and salads were good and were packed well.

We just wanted to leave a review for anyone looking to pick up large orders from here.  Be prepared to pay more than the provided quote.
They always remember my order! Love this place for lunch!

Solid build your own pizza cooked on an open flame fire. They have several Gluten free options. Around $15 for a pizza.

We each got our own because the crust is pretty thin. We came Home with just under 1/2 pizza left.

We will come back when we’re in the area looking for a tasty lunch.

This was supposed to be a quick bite but turned into a 35 minute wait for one pizza. I just had 4 people infront if me and it still took a long time. Vegan cheese was a plus but the crust is very thin. Price is ok for what you get.

Very good food. Seems staffing has gotten better though there may be a surge at different times of the year. College Town so many young adults getting pizza. Rewards program can be iffy at times. Generally good place to eat. Also, who doesn't like pizza 🍕😋

Ordered online. The pizza might very well be good but I'm still here waiting for it to be made when I placed the order online and it was marked as ready 18 minutes ago. I have to be back at work and I am stuck here waiting. Everyone else around me had a bit of a wait but they all have gotten theirs and left already. Postmates might have something to do with it as I had to order through them because otherwise they wouldn't take my card online, but either way it shouldn't be marked as delivered when it hasn't even been started yet.

Edit: the pizza itself is very good, so I will give them another chance soon and see if the service improves (maybe today was just a bad day)

Pizza quality is good, but service leaves something to be desired. Pretty slow, so be prepared to wait 20 minutes. Also double check that the pizza they say is yours is actually yours, pretty disappointing to get home and bite into a pizza that isn’t what you ordered.

Extremely expensive ($85 for 4 people with standard meals and drinks). You self-serve, and they charge for condiments/sauces. The food is not bad, but is not any better than a fast food/ fast casual chain. So many better options in the area.

First time eating here and the food was AMAZING!!!! I got the Peri Peri chicken tender bowl and it was delicious!!! I don’t like real spicy so was worried chicken may be too much but NOT AT ALL!! Just super flavorful and juicy!! Can’t wait til I’m near another to eat here again!!! That’s my only complaint is we don’t have one locally!!!

It was a great lunch because I was with a new buddy. He choose the place but I had great time.  The place needs a bit of an overhaul, some of the seats are a bit ratty.  Overall pretty good for a college place

Must order food with app on smartphone.  The employees were sitting there not doing anything when we arrived and told us they couldn't take our order and that we had to use an app.  That's ridiculous.   There are a lot of older folks that don't have those phones.   The food is good.   We are not returning until they accept cash and can take an order with a human.

reviews.author_name: Hockey mom Hockey is my sport
reviews.text: I was very unhappy with this place, the table I was seated on was split in half, we got our food and people who 4 of worker were laughing so loud that I had to cover my ears and I am not exagerating about it. Table I was seating in, it was so sticky and had to use napkins to cover it so I would be ok. If can avoid going there do so👎👎

One of the worst panda express in MD. I tried to get a white rice for my side but they don't have it and they serve really small portion for entrees and probably save the rest for the employees to bring the food home. Never coming back to this location what a joke.

Came here shortly before close since it was one of the last restaurants open in the area. Great food and generous helpings. Drink selection was very nice and staff was very thoughtful and considerate. Price was very good, we were able to split two entrees and one side among two people. Service was very quick and attentive. Will come back.

With chain restaurants, you *should* be able to expect consistency across locations, but it's rarely the case. There are worse ones where the portions are small and the staff would rather be anywhere but there. But this location has yet to disappoint. The portions are always generous, the staff nice, and the food fresh. The store is nice and bright and has a lot of seating, too.
Got there before 9:20 and they had already put away all the food and were closing. Would not let me order
IThe portion size of the food is great. It's always nice and chill in there. Food is often times fresh.

This was my first time eating here. I tried it for something quick. The fish tacos were good. The one thing I did not like was ordering from the computer at the front.  I prefer to talk to workers to get recommendations when I go to a new spot.

I've been this this District Taco a handle of times since 2018 and everytime I go it's a treat 😃😊! I fell in love with the Shrimp nachos 🦐 🍤 (pictured below), which you have to request during certain weekdays the shrimp is available (trust me... get it 🙌🏾!) May 2022 - I used my 'Too Good to Go' food waste prevention app, to buy a meal that would otherwise go to landfill. Thank you District Taco for helping preventing food waste! Next time though... don't make on the spot. Have it ready because people got things to do! Be prepared. The surprise burrito was lit though🔥 🚒 w/green peppers, steak 🐄, bacon 🥓, and rice/beans!

The staff is always so friendly and the food is great! The carnitas are my favorite. I enjoy using the outdoor seating. It is within walking distance of a splash pad and the trolly trail. Street parking is available and there is a parking lot a block away. The staff always seem to be in a good mood and like they enjoy working together. Even though orders are made on a computer the staff always asks if I need assistance. If you need to pay cash just select pay cashier when the computer asks for a credit card.

Totally dissatisfied with tacos.  It was very skimpy and extremely small for the price.  This experience has left me very disappointed.  I have had tacos that were filled with meat  lettuce  onions, peppers and soft or hard shell.  I will not order from you again.  First time order.

We love love love this place! We come here on the weekends for later breakfast when we crave enormous breakfast tacos or burritos. The tacos are so huge that my boyfriend can fit only two and I can handle only one 😁❤️ Also, we get guacamole or pico de gallo. We also get fountain drinks. Our favorite spot is outside, they do a great job of making those three tables very comfortable and cosy. They always have some plants that separate visitors from the road, which is very thoughtful and lovely. The morning sun hits those tables, so it is especially warming during colder fall days. There are also umbrellas outside. The staff is always friendly and smiling, just making the place even more attractive. And the food is delicious! Really good breakfast tacos and burritos. My pictures might not be the best but I wanted to emphasize the size and the fullness of the taco 🌮❤️

The Starbucks at the Station at Riverdale Park has its ups and downs just like all other establishments; However, they are extremely friends and learn your name if you are a regular customer. The store is always clean and the environment is relaxing.

If you need a place to sit and work I would recommend this place just get their early because everyone has the same idea and you may have a hard time finding a seat.

It does get busy from time to time just be patient with the remarkable barista’s.

I hope you enjoy your visit.

Very busy area, employees rush the order and don't make it properly. It's a bit undercook.
Hit or miss no in betweens.

Every morning I go to this store  every body knows by my name  all barista are professional when it comes to make your drink  I’m so pleased to go  there over and over o my god  the barista excellent services  fast I just order ahead I have my less then 5 minutes and she was busy but she knows what she is doing ❤️❤️❤️❤️

Staff was nice but my Frappuccino was not good. I was excited to have one because I
haven’t had it in a while. It was full of ice crystals and I couldn’t even sip it with the straw. So basically I paid almost $6 for a mild flavored cup of ice crystals with whip cream on top. Won’t be back to any Starbucks again. The coffee drinks are not the same anymore. This is not the first time this happened, I stayed away a long time
because the Frappuccino at other stores
were bad,  I came back hoping I would get a
really good one like I used to get years ago
but still got the same, lousy cup of  coffee
flavored ice crystals.

Great service from this Starbucks. It is conveniently located in the shopping center so, while shopping, you can get yourself a hot chocolate with whipped cream or whatever coffee you prefer. Parking could be a challenge specially on busy times like lunch or during the weekends. Other than that I really like this place.

My pizza was Burnt and over cooked not to mention cold after waiting for over 30 minutes since no one bother to serve me after checking that my order was ready oh forgot about the cheese bread that had no cheese 🤦🏽‍♂️
My pizza looked and tasted awful. It was soggy and had way too much salt. It also bothers me to watch team members prepare my food without wearing gloves.

I was disappointed with my experience today. The employee working, Topu, was rude! He did not appear happy at all to be there. I ordered a pizza and wings and the wings were not tossed in the BBQ sauce. He basically drizzled sauce over the plain wings as seen in the attached photo. I will not be returning to that location ever again.

I usually place an online carryout order here about 3 times a week for the last year, enough that the staff usually recognizes me when I go in to pick it up.

Today their internet ordering was down and I called to place my usual order. I asked to place my order at the regular price that I pay online. I acknowledged that the price that I pay is due to online coupons but that their internet ordering capabilities being down is no fault of mine, the manager agreed. I asked if he would credit me for the normal price that I pay and he refused.

It's a shame that I won't be ordering from Domino's anymore because their food is cheap and quick. I believe that I was rational and respectful but the manager refused to do anything for me.
Great tasting as usual but they've reduced the number of toppings for their $7.99 promotion

name: Taco Bell
vicinity: Glenn L. Martin Hall Campus Drive, 8428 Baltimore Avenue, College Park

reviews.text:
Great place for comfort (not healthy, I would presume) food. We have been visiting this Taco Bell for over 20 years and love it. The staff are very friendly and accommodative of our families dietary needs.

They have just installed these new automated kiosks and it's very good as well. We end up eating more than we should packing up unhealthy pounds, but love ever minute eating our food 😎

The staff is very friendly. They have accommodated me on many occasions when I have requested minor changes be made to something I am purchasing.

And it's Taco Bell. It's cheap and will fill you up.
Hours suck, but convenient for those who have classes in the engineering and math buildings who dont want to walk to a dining hall between classes
They're always big mad when you don't pickup your order within literally a picosecond of them calling your number
I mean it's a Taco Bell so 3/5 is pretty much a perfect score.
